It's not the rattlers, it's the black cattle.  The rattlers you can drive
right over, but 1500 pounds of Angus steer will ruin your whole day.

I'd never drive my bus after dark in Mexico or on open range highways in
the US.  Just too risky and you can't see the scenery!

